last_episode_to_air.name: Super Shopper Max / Ruby's Time Capsule

name: Max and Ruby
overview: Meet two funny bunny siblings, the energetic and mischievous Max, and the patient, smart and goal-oriented Ruby. The show models empowering messages by showing Max and Ruby playing together and resolving their differences respectfully and supportively.

episodes.name: Max's Bedtime
episodes.overview: Max can't sleep until he finds his red rubber elephant. Later, he spies it must have been under his bed the whole time.NOTE: At the end, Max says "Good Night, Ruby." This is one of two instances that Max speaks a full sentence.

episodes.name: Max's Bath
episodes.overview: Max is still hungry after his lunch is all over him instead of in him, and Ruby decides to give him a bath, but unfortunately, he uses sherbet tubs and a grape juice glass as a boat, and that manages to get him dirtier than before, so Ruby gives him a shower. After his shower, he points out that Ruby's clothes have been stained, meaning she needs to wash now.

episodes.name: Ruby's Piano Practice
episodes.overview: Ruby has a piano practice, and Max can't find his fire truck. Ruby then tries to make Max play with different toys but at the end Ruby realizes that Max's fire truck must have been in the piano the whole time.

episodes.name: Hide and Seek
episodes.overview: Ruby tries to teach Max to play Hide-and-Seek, but when they play, Max is too little to understand the rules and he does not want to give Ruby a turn to hide. When Ruby unsuccessfully tries to explain to him that it is her turn to hide since Max already had a turn, Max takes his chances to hide when Ruby isn't looking.

episodes.name: Max's Wormcake
episodes.overview: Ruby wants to plant marigolds in a garden but its the same place Max has chosen to make a "worm cake", a mud-pie consisting of soaked soil, stones, and worms. He uses all her marigold-planting materials in his worm cake, but then he gives the worm cake back to Ruby, where it's used for a good cause.

episodes.name: Louise's Secret
episodes.overview: Ruby can't wait for the phone to ring, because Louise has a big secret to tell her. But when the phone finally rings, Max chooses that exact time to play with his loud toys.

episodes.name: Max Misses the Bus
episodes.overview: Ruby is all ready to catch the next bus to Louise's house, but Max wants to stay home and play with his toys. Ruby tries to convince Max to come by promising to bring his toys along, but they miss bus after bus because of Max's antics. Will the bunnies arrive at Louise's safely?

episodes.name: Ruby's Leaf Collection
episodes.overview: Ruby decides to start a collection of leaves, and really wants to find a rare leaf known as the big tooth aspen leaf. But Max keeps getting in the way of finding the leaf. Will Ruby be able to complete her collection?

episodes.name: Max's Breakfast
episodes.overview: Max isn't eager he'll like his breakfast, a bunny-side-up egg, and wants strawberries instead. Ruby is distracted when Max tries attempts to hide his egg.

episodes.name: Ruby's Clubhouse
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise build a clubhouse, but Max thinks he can sneak in just because Ruby and Louise are not in the clubhouse. Later, Ruby builds Max his own clubhouse.NOTE: This is one of few instances that Ruby's passion is used against her rather than dovetailing with Max's.

episodes.name: Max's Rainy Day
episodes.overview: Ruby and Max want to go outside to play in the rain, but Max wants to go out in his sunny day clothes. Ruby tries to get Max to put on a raincoat, but by the time both of the bunnies are ready to go out, the rain clouds have cleared and the sun is out. Can Max and Ruby still have fun in the rain? No. But they can have fun with the hose!

episodes.name: The Blue Tarantula
episodes.overview: Max insists on Ruby reading him a scary mystery story before bed. After some hesitation, Ruby agrees to, and reads Max a story about the blue tarantula, who crawls on little bunnies at night when they are asleep and bites them, causing them to die. Max stays up all night in fear of the tarantula. Will Ruby find a way to get him to go to sleep?

episodes.name: Max's Halloween
episodes.overview: Max wants to be something scary for Halloween like a Vampire. But Ruby would rather have him a prince to go with her princess costume believing that Max will scare Grandma when they trick or treat at her house.

episodes.name: Camp Out
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby are having a camp out but Max wants to sleep outside instead of the tent. When Max stuffs all his toys in the tent, He and Ruby are forced to sleep outside, much to his delight.

episodes.name: Quiet, Max!
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby go to the Huffingtons' house to play while Baby Huffington is napping. Max wants to listen to the radio, starting a ruckus, and causes Baby Huffington to wake up and cry. How will the bunnies stop the baby from crying?

episodes.name: Max's Picnic
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise are bird watching but Max wants his cupcake. Later, he finds a speckled warbler, feeds it his cupcake and shows the warbler to Ruby and Louise.

episodes.name: Ruby's Merit Badge
episodes.overview: Ruby wants to earn her First Aid merit badge. When Ruby tries to get her merit badge by bandaging dolls, she suggests she bandage a real person. But that real person is Max...and Max's antics cause Ruby to earn a different badge.

episodes.name: Max Cleans Up
episodes.overview: Ruby wants Max to clean his room, and Max stuffs the mess into his pocket instead of placing his toys and things where they belong. What's going to happen when Ruby finds out?

episodes.name: Max's Apple
episodes.overview: Ruby is all ready to catch the next bus to Louise's house, but Max wants to stay home and play with his toys. Ruby tries to convince Max to come by promising to bring his toys along, but they miss bus after bus because of Max's antics. Will the bunnies arrive at Louise's safely?

episodes.name: Bunny Cakes
episodes.overview: Ruby wants to make Grandma an 'Angel Surprise Cake with Raspberry Fluff Icing' for Grandma's birthday, but Max wants to make Grandma an earthworm cake. Ruby thinks that Grandma will like her cake best, but Grandma really appreciates both cakes!

episodes.name: Max's Cuckoo Clock
episodes.overview: While Mrs. Huffington is out at her garden tea party in the backyard, Ruby's job is to put Baby Huffington to sleep. But Max wants to play with the Huffingtons' cuckoo clock, and the sound of the clock might wake the baby...

episodes.name: Goodnight Max
episodes.overview: Max cannot go to sleep, and keeps waking up in the middle of the night. His antics cause his clothes to get stained and dirty, and Ruby can't get Max to sleep. Eventually, Ruby's Walkie-Talkie Bear toy gets Max some shut-eye.

episodes.name: Ruby's Jewelry Box
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise are making a Queen of Egypt tiara, and Ruby is not in her room. Max tries to look in Ruby's jewelry box, but is caught by Ruby, who doesn't want Max in her room. Will Max ever see what's inside the box?

episodes.name: Bunny Money
episodes.overview: Ruby has saved a wallet full of money to buy Grandma a music box with skating ballerinas on top for her birthday, but shopping with Max costs more than Ruby planned.

episodes.name: Max's Rocket Run
episodes.overview: Max wants to sled down a large hill called Rocket Run with his toboggan, but Ruby and Louise only allow Max to go on Bunny Hill, a small hill used as a sledding location for younger bunnies. What will happen?

episodes.name: Bunny Party
episodes.overview:
At Grandma's birthday party, Ruby has invited her dolls. To get his own toys into the party, Max disguises them as Ruby's dolls. 
NOTE: Max does not speak in this episode.

episodes.name: Max's Birthday
episodes.overview: Max gets so many presents for his birthday that he forgets to open one. So Ruby opens it for him and finds a "wind-up lobster." Max is in for the chase of his life, only he's the one being chased -- by the lobster!

episodes.name: Max's Christmas
episodes.overview: Max is full of questions when Ruby hurries to bed on Christmas Eve so that Santa Claus can come. No one ever stays up to see Santa. No one except Max.

episodes.name: Ruby's Snow Queen
episodes.overview: Max wants to play with a screaming, green alien-gorilla, but Ruby insists that he helps her create a snow queen to welcome Grandma. After the snow queen is finished, Max's gorilla toy has vanished. Will the bunnies find out that the alien gorilla was run over when Ruby and Max were building the snow queen and is currently inside the snow formation?

episodes.name: Ruby's Lemonade Stand
episodes.overview: Ruby's Lemonade Stand. Ruby and Louise are having a lemonade stand for Bunny Scouts.

episodes.name: Max Drives Away
episodes.overview: It's breakfast time, and Max wants ice cream. Ruby says that nobody eats ice cream for breakfast. So Max drives off in his pedal car and goes to the only person who understands.

episodes.name: Max's New Suit
episodes.overview: Max refuses to get dressed in his new suit for a party he's invited too.

episodes.name: Ruby's Rummage Sale
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise are having a rummage sale to raise money for a Bunny Scout field trip, but Max wants to keep the toys Ruby and Louise want to sell.

episodes.name: Max's Chocolate Chicken
episodes.overview: Max wants to eat a chocolate chicken an Easter bunny left on a birdbath.

episodes.name: Ruby Flies a Kite
episodes.overview: Ruby tries to fly a kite.

episodes.name: Ruby's Beauty Shop
episodes.overview: Louise and Ruby decide to pretend they own a salon, but Max is the customer!

episodes.name: Ruby's Magic Act
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise are practicing their magic act for the Bunny Scouts talent show, and they need Max to be their volunteer from the audience. Max wants to know how they do their tricks, but Ruby and Louise insist on 'magician code of honor'. In the end, Max is the one who surprises them with his own magic trick!

episodes.name: Max's Valentine
episodes.overview: Valentine's Day is a busy time for Ruby and Louise, who make special Valentine cards for their friends. Max wants to make a Valentine, but he's too little to use scissors and glue. Ruby gives Max the important job of taking her Valentines to the mailbox, and Max ends up making a special Valentine delivery of his own.

episodes.name: Super Max
episodes.overview: Ruby is preparing to go for a picnic with Louise and her dolly Sally-Swims-a-Lot, but Max is listening to his favorite radio show, Super Bunny. When Sally suddenly goes missing, it's up to Super Max to come to the rescue.

episodes.name: Max's Work of Art
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise are painting pictures for the Bunny Scout art exhibit -- and they use Max as a model. But Max doesn't want to model -- he wants to paint!

episodes.name: Max Meets Morris
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise think that Max and Morris (Louise's toddler cousin) will become friends while they make a banner for the Bunny Scout Picnic.

episodes.name: Ruby's Scavenger Hunt
episodes.overview: The Bunny Scout leader has organized a scavenger hunt in the park for all the Bunny Scouts, but Max keeps interrupting Ruby's search.

episodes.name: Ruby's Hiccups
episodes.overview: Ruby has the hiccups and Max can't find his monster mask.

episodes.name: The Big Picture
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby have a picture to take and send to their Grandma but all Max wants to do is chase a butterfly.

episodes.name: Ruby's Stage Show
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise decide to put on a show for Grandma, but Max wants to wear his dragon mask instead.

episodes.name: Max's Froggy Friend
episodes.overview: Making friends with a frog in the creek, Max wants to take it home with him. But Ruby is planning a tea party for Grandma, and that's no place for a froggy.

episodes.name: Max's Music
episodes.overview: Ruby, Valerie and Louise try to be a trio called Ruby's Red Hot Trio playing "The Farmer in the Dell", but they keep getting interrupted by Max's own music playing.

episodes.name: Max Gets Wet
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby fix their garden up when it shrivels up but Max wants to go swimming in his pool and he has to wait one half hour.

episodes.name: Ruby's Tea Party
episodes.overview: Ruby wants to have a tea party with her dollies, but Max wants to play pirates.

episodes.name: Max Is It
episodes.overview: Max wants to eat his Dribbler, but is it in a game of Freeze Tag with Ruby, Louise, and Valerie, and they're impossible for Max to get.

episodes.name: Ruby's Science Project
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise are doing a science project and Max wants candy.

episodes.name: Ruby's Panda Prize
episodes.overview: At the carnival, Ruby wants to win a panda bear prize and Max wants jelly balls.

episodes.name: Ruby's Roller Skates
episodes.overview: Ruby wants to learn how to roller-skate and is interrupted by Max wanting his Tow-a-Ton Tow Truck.

episodes.name: Ghost Bunny
episodes.overview: The Bunny Scout leaders are having a jamboree, and the highlight (after s'mores) is telling ghost stories around the campfire.

episodes.name: Max's Bug Salad
episodes.overview: Max wants to add bugs to Grandma's gelatin salad.

episodes.name: Ruby's Beach Party
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise want to have a beach party in Max and Ruby's yard, but Max and Morris want to play dump-truck.

episodes.name: Super Max to the Rescue
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise want to play circus in the yard. When Super Max sees his red rubber elephant in peril at the circus, he's to the rescue!

episodes.name: Max's Dragon Shirt
episodes.overview: At the department store, Max wants a dragon shirt, but Ruby only has $5 to buy him a brand-new pair of overalls.

episodes.name: Max's Rabbit Racer
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise are taking baton twirling lessons from Mrs. Huffington, and Max is entertaining himself and Baby Huffington with his Rabbit Racer.

episodes.name: Roger's Choice
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise want to play with Ruby's best male friend Roger Piazza but Max wants Roger to play cars with him.

episodes.name: Ruby's Pajama Party
episodes.overview: Ruby, Louise and Valerie are having a pajama party, but Max wants to come too.

episodes.name: Baby Max
episodes.overview: Louise and Ruby try to get Max to pretend to be a baby, but Max doesn't like that game. He just wants to go on the playground slide.

episodes.name: Bunny Scout Brownies
episodes.overview: Max keeps sampling the Bunny Scout brownies Ruby has to sell.

episodes.name: Max's Shadow
episodes.overview: Ruby and Valerie are trying to make a ballerina poster. Max is playing with his shadow, which keeps disappearing in the sun.

episodes.name: Max Remembers
episodes.overview: Discovering a string tied around Max's finger, Ruby leaps to the assumption that he's supposed to remember something.

episodes.name: Ruby's Candy Store
episodes.overview: Ruby wants to be the owner of the candy store, but unfortunately, she gets to know the candy's tastes a little too well.

episodes.name: Max's Check Up
episodes.overview: Louise and Ruby play doctor. Max is chosen as the patient, but he wants to play with his markers.

episodes.name: Max's Prize
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise look for special things for Ruby's charm bracelet.

episodes.name: Space Max
episodes.overview: Ruby, Valerie and Louise are going to make a float for the Bunny Scout Parade, but Max wants to play spaceman.

episodes.name: Ruby's Figure Eight
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise go ice-skating to try to make figure-eights.

episodes.name: Ruby's Surprise Party
episodes.overview: Ruby plans a surprise party for Louise, and she employs Max as the lookout.

episodes.name: Ruby's Tent
episodes.overview: Ruby and Valerie try to put a tent together despite interruptions from... Super Max!

episodes.name: Ruby Writes a Story
episodes.overview: Ruby needs absolute quiet while she tries to write a story. But Max wants to play cowboy.

episodes.name: Max's Dominoes
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise want to earn their hospitality badge by hosting a Bunny Scout meeting.

episodes.name: Grandma's Attic
episodes.overview: In Grandma's attic, Ruby is delighted to try on old clothes and Max finds an old chest that nobody ever goes into (according to Grandma).

episodes.name: Max's Thanksgiving
episodes.overview: Ruby and Max are at Grandma's to help with Thanksgiving dinner. Ruby is thrilled to help decorate, but Max just wants to sample Grandma's famous stuffing.

episodes.name: Max's Pretend Friend
episodes.overview: Ruby thinks that Max has a pretend friend.

episodes.name: Fireman Max
episodes.overview: Ruby wants to practice jumping rope for the Bunny Scout jump-a-thon, but Max wants to play fireman, and he keeps tripping her up.

episodes.name: Ruby's Easter Bonnet
episodes.overview: Ruby is making an Easter Bonnet for the Bunny Scout Easter Bonnet contest, while Max tries to teach Froggy to hop.

episodes.name: Max's Easter Parade
episodes.overview: Ruby is decorating Easter Eggs but Max wants to see an Easter parade.

episodes.name: Max & the Easter Bunny
episodes.overview: Ruby and the rest of the Bunny Scouts are eager to participate in the annual Easter Egg Hunt.

episodes.name: Ruby's Hippity Hop Dance
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise tries to learn the Hippity Hop Dance. Meanwhile, Roger teaches Max how to play football.

episodes.name: Ruby's Bird Bath
episodes.overview: Ruby tries to make an environmentally-correct bird bath for a Bunny Scout merit badge, but Max keeps putting bath toys in it.

episodes.name: Super Max Saves the World
episodes.overview: Max (as Super Bunny) and Morris (as Zoom-Zoom) pretend to be superheroes while Ruby and Louise make a science project.

episodes.name: Ruby Delivers
episodes.overview: Ruby must deliver some fliers for Bunny Scout cupcakes.

episodes.name: Getting Crabby at the Beach
episodes.overview: Ruby tries to collect seashells.

episodes.name: Max Babysits
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby are going to the Huffingtons' house to look after Baby Huffington, who seems to like noisy toys instead of gentle sounds.

episodes.name: Max's Fire Flies
episodes.overview: Max wants to catch fire flies.

episodes.name: Max & Ruby's Fashion Show
episodes.overview: Ruby, Louise and Max decide to have their own fashion show, but Max just wants to dress up as a pirate.

episodes.name: Rubyâ€™s Sing-a-long
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby want to be in a talent show. Ruby wants to sing and play the piano at the same time, and Max wants to sing too.

episodes.name: Ruby's Safari
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise go on a safari, but Max thinks his toys would be perfect. Well, his red rubber elephant seems perfect for the safari.

episodes.name: Max's Mudbath
episodes.overview: Max wants to play in the mud.

episodes.name: Max's Lost Lizard
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise worry when their chameleon  disappears out of the cage, while Max enjoys its abilities.

episodes.name: Surprise Ruby
episodes.overview: It's Ruby's birthday and Ruby expects her friends to throw her a surprise party at their home. But Ruby must give chase when Max makes off with her birthday tiara.

episodes.name: Ruby's Birthday Party
episodes.overview: Ruby's friends throw her a birthday party at Grandma's house. But before they can have cake, Ruby insists they must play some birthday games first.

episodes.name: Ruby's Birthday Present
episodes.overview: Ruby unwraps her birthday presents and plans to save all the pretty wrapping paper. Meanwhile, Max tries to wrap a gift for his sister.

episodes.name: Max's Ant Farm
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby are on a chase to get Max's ants back in the ant farm, before Ruby's guests notice.

episodes.name: Sugar Plum Max
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise practice The Sugar Plum Fairy, while Max tries various attempts to get a sugar plum.

episodes.name: Ruby's Puppet Show
episodes.overview: Max attempts to get a role in Ruby and Louise's puppet show.

episodes.name: Ruby's Loose Tooth
episodes.overview: Ruby and Max try to search for Ruby's loose tooth that was lost.

episodes.name: Ruby Scores
episodes.overview: Ruby tries to play soccer, but keeps getting surrounded by Max's robots.

episodes.name: Ruby's Sandcastle
episodes.overview: Ruby wants to make a sandcastle, but Max wants to get in the water.

episodes.name: Grandma's Berry Patch
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby pick raspberries, blueberries, and blackberries so Grandma can make her special surprise berry recipe..."mushed berry smoothies".

episodes.name: Ruby's Bunny Scout Banner
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise paint a banner for their Bunny Scout parade, but Max constantly interrupts them.

episodes.name: Ruby's Detective Agency
episodes.overview: Grandma has a surprise for Ruby, but before Ruby can go to Grandma's house she must solve the mystery of Mrs. Quack's disappearance.

episodes.name: Max's Rocket Racer
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby are at the East Bunny Hop Summer Fair. When Ruby and Louise point out that Max is below the line (height) for the Rocket Racer ride, Max sets out to find ways to be taller.

episodes.name: Max's Candy Apple
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby are at the East Bunny Hop Fall Fair where there's races, food, and prizes. Max has his sights set on a candy apple, but Ruby insists she and Max participate in some races first to win a prize.

episodes.name: Max's Blast Off!
episodes.overview: Ruby and Louise host a special bunny scout meeting to celebrate Bunny Scout Leader's birthday. The meeting gets that extra special touch when Super Bunny and Zoom Zoom "help".

episodes.name: Max's Jack-o-Lantern
episodes.overview: Max (vampire) and Ruby (fairy godmother) dress up for a Halloween party at their home. Before their guests arrive, Ruby tells Max to design a pumpkin face for Grandma to carve, but Ruby insists it must be a happy, smiley pumpkin.

episodes.name: Max & Ruby's Perfect Pumpkin
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby are in Mr. Piazza's store in search of the perfect Halloween pumpkin.

episodes.name: Max's Big Boo!
episodes.overview: Max (vampire) and Ruby (fairy godmother) prepare to go trick-or-treating. Max takes every opportunity to scare Ruby, but Ruby knows all his tricks.

episodes.name: Max & Ruby's Christmas Tree
episodes.overview: Ruby and Max decorate their Christmas tree, but Max thinks toys would be beautiful on it.

episodes.name: Grandma's Present
episodes.overview: Max and Ruby buy Grandma a Christmas present.

episodes.name: Max & Ruby's Snow Plow
episodes.overview: Ruby tries to shovel the snow off the lawn to make room for Grandma to get to their house.

episodes.name: Max's Mix Up
episodes.overview: Max switches his snow clothes with Morris.

episodes.name: Max's Snow Bunny
episodes.overview: Max tries to find out if the snow bunny is real.

episodes.name: Max's Snow Day
episodes.overview: Max wants to go outside in the snow, but there's a blizzard!

episodes.name: Max's Preschool, Grandma's Storytime Sleepover
episodes.overview:
Max creates a good impression on his new preschool class.

Max and Ruby have a special camp out story extravaganza when Grandma comes to visit.

episodes.name: Ruby's Teacher / Max's Art Time
episodes.overview:
Ruby, Valerie and Louise want to create a special card for their new teacher.

Max and his classmates paint self-portraits. Meanwhile, Ruby works as Miss Bunty's assistant helper for the day.

episodes.name: Show and Tell / The Whirligig
episodes.overview:
Max wants to bring his toy Tin-Froggy to school for Show and Tell, however Ruby tries to convince him to choose something else.

While playing with Max's new Whirligig toy, Max & his classmate Lily help Ruby with keeping a flock of crows out of Ruby's garden.

episodes.name: Max's Rocket / Max! Bam! Boom!
episodes.overview:
Mr. Bunny gives Max & Ruby a cardboard box to share. Max wants turn a cardboard box into a pretend rocket ship as Ruby and Louise want to turn it into Rapunzel's Tower.

Max creates a one-bunny-band, giving Ruby, Louise, and Valerie something special for their talent show performance.

episodes.name: Max Whistles / Ruby's Photo Op
episodes.overview:
Max learns how to whistle.

Ruby wants to take a perfect picture to give to Grandma for Grandparents Day.

episodes.name: Grandma's Surprise / Costume Day
episodes.overview:
Max tries to peek at a surprise Grandma left for the bunnies.

Max wants to be Super Bunny for the costume day, not a king.

episodes.name: Max's Skateboard / Super Butterfly
episodes.overview:
Max wants to learn to skateboard while Ruby sets up for a Bunny Scout meeting.

Max's classmates create butterfly wings, but he wants to be a caterpillar.

episodes.name: Ruby Juggles / Max and Priya
episodes.overview:
Ruby learns to deal with Max's constant interruptions.

Max discovers that being his fun, silly self is the best way to get shy Priya to open up.

episodes.name: Dino Hunter Max / Ruby's Solar System
episodes.overview:
Max disrupts Ruby's party by digging in the backyard for dinosaur bones.

Max adds to Ruby's solar system model when he decides to play a ball game indoors.

episodes.name: Fun in the Sun / Max the Detective
episodes.overview:
Ruby, Louise, Max, and Lily discover a new sport, kite-boarding.

Detective Max is on the case when Ruby misplaces her diary.
